The Lotta Sv√§rd emblem (on the left) designed by Eric Wasstr√∂m in 1921 was based on an earlier suggestion (sketch on the right) by Akseli Gallen-Kallela.

Even though the organization was technically founded in 1918, it was part of the White Guard (Finnish: Suojeluskunta; hence the S in Gallen-Kallela's design) until it became a separate organization in 1921.

The name of the organization comes from Johan Ludvig Runeberg's (1804 ‚Äì 1877) 1853 poem of a fictional character of the same name, a patriotic and motherly figure who helped soldiers in the Finnish War of 1808 ‚Äî 1809 against Russia. The poem was published in 1860 as the fourth poem of the second volume of Runeberg's magnum opus The Tales of Ensign St√•l.

At least three different women have been suggested to have served as the inspiration for the character Lotta Sv√§rd, but it is quite likely that Runeberg did not base it on any one particular woman.

At best, the organization had 240,000 members, including around 50,000 Junior Lottas aged 8 ‚àí 17.

War with China will result in huge losses for the U.S.
  
Simulations by the CSIS International Security Program show uninspiring results for the U.S. military: just one month of conflict would be comparable in casualties to 20 years of war in Iraq and Afghanistan.  
  
"Such losses would damage U.S. global positions for many years," report authors Mark Kansian, Matthew Kansian and Eric Heginbotham state.  
  
A comment from retired U.S. Navy Capt. William Toti is also cited:
  
"I'm afraid we've awakened a sleeping giant. They have more ships than we do. They have more industrial capacity," he said, adding that the United States is simply not ready for such a conflict.   
  
The report was released after a U.S. general called for preparations for war with China in the next two years.
